<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Description</div>
<dl id="n54"><dt><a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm">N54 (VI.B.45)</a> <cite>Remember G</cite> </dt> <dd> <ul><li>DATE: January-April 1938 : Paris, Zurich. </li><li>DETAILS: 156 pages unruled, heavy paper 17.5 x 12 cm. The contents pages of Joyce's copy of <cite>Moore's Melodies</cite> forms an appendix to this notebook. </li><li>First use: revision of II.3&sect;4-5 for <cite>transition</cite>, Book I galleys (second set), and II.1-11.3&sect;1 galleys. <br>Note: Joyce and Gilbert were observed using this notebook in April 1938 (see Mercanton memoir, <a name="15Apr1938" href="../../ff/fbiog/fwlett.htm#15Apr1938">15 April</a> 1938), the words in question coming from the Finno-Urgic portion of the <a name="MCLM" href="../../../f/ff/fdra/fdex.htm#dexMCLM">Languages</a> source. </li><li>PHOTO-REPLICATE: <cite>James Joyce Archive</cite> (New York: Garland, 1978), vol. 40 </li><li><a href="../../../f/ff/fdra/fdex.htm#dexn54">Sources</a> </li></ul> </dd> </dl>
